  <description type="morphology">Leaf blades thin, base cordate or subtruncate, surfaces puberulent, sessile-glandular.  Racemes pen-dent, 15–40-flowered, 5–15 cm.  Flowers: hypanthium rose or rarely white, tubular to slightly campanulate, 5–7 mm; sepals reflexed, pink to white, lanceolate; petals connivent, white or pink, oblong to almost square; stamens as long as petals; ovary stipitate-glandular; styles glabrous.  Berries ovoid, 3–6(–10) mm, densely stipitate-glandular.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Jan-May.</description>
